page.title: 20Bramhope: Ecology (Plants)
page.content: In our area there are many species of trees growing in woods,gardens and recreational areas.The most common are:{ash,beech,elderberry,hawthorn, {holly,horse-chesnut,oak and silver {birch.}Other species include:{alder, {birdcherry,cedar,copper beech,cyprus, {laurel,conifers,poplar,rhododendron, {rowan,sycamore,willow and yew.}The most common plants observed were:{ {buttercups,clover,cow-parsley, {dandelions,daisies,dog roses,nettles, and many grasses. These plants were all seen:{agrimony,burdock,bracken, {broom,brambles,bird-weed,bishop's {weed,catmint,cock'scomb,coltsfoot, {cornflower,chickweed,dog daisy,false {oat,flowering currant,ground elder, {flea sedge,forget-me-not,fern,gorse, {groundsel,horsetails,ivy,Jack-by-the- {hedge,ladies smock,lichens,plantains, {primrose,ragwort}and{red campion.
